# Shell scripts and git hooks MUST stay LF-only. With core.autocrlf=true (common on Windows),
# a checkout would otherwise rewrite them to CRLF — and a CRLF bash script silently fails
# (`#!/usr/bin/env bash\r` → bad interpreter), disabling the pre-commit guard + the shipped
# SessionStart hook without any error. eol=lf pins storage AND checkout to LF. See docs/PROCESS.md §9.
*.sh        text eol=lf
.husky/**   text eol=lf
